    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "Anthomyiidae, Fanniidae and Muscidae (Diptera) from the Juan Fernández Archipelago (Chile): 60 years after Willi Hennig’s contributions" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1209027>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1209031>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1209035>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1209033>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1209039>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1209037> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1209027>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–11. Anthomyia limbinervis (Macquart, 1843): (1) scutellum with pale cilia ventrally (black arrow); (2) wing, ventral view; (3) costal vein ciliated ventrally, ventral view; Delia platura (Meigen, 1826): (4) male, hind femur, posterior view; (5) wing, ventral view; (6) costal vein bare ventrally, ventral view; Fannia anthracina (Walker, 1836): (7) wing, ventral view, subcostal sinuous (white arrow), vein A 2 strongly curved (black arrow); Fannia hennigi sp. n.: (8) male, coxa ciliated, posterior surface (blackarrow); Lispoides insularis Hennig, 1957:(9) abdomen, lateral view, katepisternum 2+1 (white arrow), lower calypter twice as long as upper one (blackarrow); Notoschoenomyza kuscheli Hennig, 1955: (10) abdomen, lateral view, katepisternum 1+1+1 (white arrow), calypters with similar length (black arrow); Syllimnophora lispomima Hennig, 1955: (11) female, head, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1209027/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1209031>
    dc:description "FIGURES 16–17. Fannia anthracina (Walker, 1836):(16) male and (17) female, lateral view.Scale:0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1209031/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1209035>
    dc:description "FIGURES 24–32. Fannia hennigi sp. n., paratype male: (24) hind leg, anterior view; (25) hind leg, posterior view; (26) sternite 5, dorsal view; (27) epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli, dorsal view; (28) epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli, lateral view; (29) hypandrium and associated structures, dorsal view. Female:(30) spermathecae; (31)terminal segments of abdomen, dorsal view; (32) terminal segments of abdomen, ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1209035/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1209033>
    dc:description "FIGURES 18–23. Fannia hennigi sp. n., male holotype: (18) head, anterior view; (19) lateral view; (20) dorsal view; (21) male abdomen, posterior view; female paratype:(22) head anterior view; (23) lateral view. Scale: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1209033/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1209039>
    dc:description "FIGURES 39–44. Notoschoenomyza kuscheli Hennig, 1955: (39) female, lateral view. Psilochaeta chalybea (Wiedemann, 1830): (40) male and (41) female, lateral view. Schoenomyzina emdeni Hennig, 1955: (42) female. Syllimnophora lispomima Hennig, 1955: (43) male and (44) female, lateral view. Scale: 1.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1209039/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1209037>
    dc:description "FIGURES33–38.Hydrotaea cyaneiventris (Macquart, 1851):(33) male and (34) female,lateral view.Limnophora patagonica Malloch, 1934: (35) male and (36) female, lateral view. Lispoides insularis Hennig, 1957: (37) male and (38) female, lateral view.Scale:1.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1209037/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

